snippet.textDisplay: After Madari, this is the next best Clinton Cerejo composition I like. Remember, Coke Studio is all about experimentation & I'm amazed on how well Clinton has done this. I remember hearing Mory Kante's Yeke Yeke with Santana & always wondered why Indian musicians never experiment with local folk artistes. There you go, Coke Studio made it possible. Sawan Khan's voice represents the Rajasthani folk to the fullest & Clinton simply rocks in this high energy composition. Thumbs up !

I am not trying to start a debate or something like that, just stating facts, you can do your own research....

Sindhi was invented by Aryans in 3000bc, in Indus valley. The name India comes from Indus. Sindh reference comes in indian national anthem too.

Urdu was invented by persians, and it is one of the official launguages of India.

Pakistan was created by 1947, till then there was only India.
